                                <layout>The left-hand edge of the slab possibly features an ogham inscription below a <rs type="decoration">key pattern</rs>. The front face is decorated with a <rs type="decoration">cross</rs> with <q>'a <rs type="decoration">cloaked man</rs> clutching a small square shield and a staff on one side of the shaft and a <rs type="decoration">hunting scene</rs> on the other'</q> (Fraser 2008, 56). The back face depicts <rs type="decoration">two huntsmen on horseback</rs> with a <rs type="decoration">double-disc and Z-rod symbol</rs> accompanying the upper figure (ibid).</layout>
